sec.p:
The terrestrial magnetosphere plays the role of a magnetic obstacle with respect to the continuous and super-fast-magnetosonic flow of the solar wind. A permanent bow shock results, brakes/deviates the flow and allows a transition from the super-fast-magnetosonic to sub-fast-magnetosonic regime. Due to its curved shape, the features of the shock front drastically change according to the local angle (ΘBn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
