				\begin{document}$2 \times 10^{6}\mbox{ km}$\end{document}. Masters et al. (2008) reported Cassini electron plasma and magnetic field observations of two HFAs at Saturn. See Fig. 10 for an example. The events occurred at the intersection of IMF discontinuities with the planetary bow shock. By contrast to HFAs observed elsewhere, there were electron density enhancements within the core region of the events. Event dimensions were again large, 2 and 6 Saturnian radii. As shown in Fig. 12, the event dimension at different planets increases with increasing distance from the Sun. Fig. 10
