				\begin{document}$_{\parallel }$\end{document} bow shock on at least one side, and a few HFAs have Q⊥ bow shock on both sides (Schwartz et al. 2000; Facskó et al. 2009; Wang et al. 2013b). One possibility is that as the bow shock is curved, HFAs may form in the Q∥\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
