The figure illustrates a number of typical properties that are consistent with observations of HFAs. The interior of the HFA-like structure is strongly heated and almost stagnant. Note that this simulation is in the de Hoffmann-Teller frame of the original shock in which the HFA is just expanding but not moving along the original shock. In the normal incidence frame the structure is actually moving downward along the shock with a velocity that depends on the solar wind speed and ΘBn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
