Analytical linear theories have been derived for mode conversion at the magnetopause (Johnson and Cheng 1997; Johnson et al. 2001) based on a kinetic-MHD model, which uses Ohm’s law and the momentum equations obtained from the gyrokinetic equations. Based on the quasilinear theory, the diffusion coefficient for the KAWs under typical magnetopause conditions is on the order of D⊥∼109−10m2/s\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
